#  Code for hierarchical dependence analysis linking large-scale climate variability modes, regional climate, and tree growth

## Code availability

The source code used for the analyses is openly available in this GitHub repository.

The repository provides the complete workflow for quantifying hierarchical relationships among large-scale climate variability modes, regional climate conditions, and tree-ring growth responses.
## Overview

This repository contains the computational workflow used to investigate hierarchical relationships among coupled large-scale climate variability modes (LCVMs), regional climate (temperature and precipitation), and tree growth (tree-ring chronology).

The workflow integrates nonlinear dependence analysis, machine learning, and statistical modeling approaches, including Vine Copula models, long short-term memory (LSTM) neural networks, permutation-based contribution analysis, and multivariate statistical analysis.


## Workflow

The analytical workflow includes:

1. Quantification of dependence structures among large-scale climate variability modes using Vine Copula models.

2. Modeling hierarchical climate-growth interactions using long short-term memory (LSTM) neural networks.

3. Evaluation of climate-growth relationships by integrating large-scale climate variability modes, regional climate conditions, and radial tree growth responses.

4. Quantification of the relative contributions of large-scale climate variability modes to regional climate and tree-growth responses using permutation-based approaches.

5. Evaluation of model performance and robustness using statistical metrics and permutation tests.


